-- Sony aims to sell 17 million LCD TVs in 2008/09
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2008 2:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/14/us-sony-sales-idUSTKF00315120080514

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Sony Corp ( 6758.T ) said on Wednesday it aimed to sell 17 million liquid crystal display TVs in the year to March 2009, up from 10.6 million units sold in the year that ended on March 31. 

 The Japanese electronics and entertainment conglomerate said it targets PlayStation 3 videogame console sales of 10 million units this year compared with 9.24 million in the year just ended. Sony, which competes with Microsoft Corp ( MSFT.O ) and Nintendo Co Ltd 7974.OS in the global videogame industry, also aims to sell 15 million PlayStation Portable handheld game machines this year, up from 13.9 million units in the 2007/08 business year. (Reporting by  Kiyoshi Takenaka ; Editing by  Hugh Lawson )